###########################################################################
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
Let
$PAR
\[
A = \left[
\begin{array}{rrr}
$a11 & $a12 & $a13\\
$a21 & $a22 & $a23\\
$a31 & $a32 & $a33
\end{array}
\right] \qquad 
B = \left[
\begin{array}{rrr}
$b11 & $b12 & $b13\\
$b21 & $b22 & $b23\\
$b31 & $b32 & $b33
\end{array}
\right] 
\]
$PAR
\[
C = \left[
\begin{array}{rrrrrr}
$a11 & $a12 & $a13 & 0 & 0 & 0\\
$a21 & $a22 & $a23 & 0 & 0 & 0\\
$a31 & $a32 & $a33 & 0 & 0 & 0\\
0 & 0 & 0 & $b11 & $b12 & $b13\\
0 & 0 & 0 & $b21 & $b22 & $b23\\
0 & 0 & 0 & $b31 & $b32 & $b33
\end{array}
\right]
\]
$PAR
Find the inverses of \(A\), \(B\) and \(C\).
$BCENTER
\{ mbox( '\(A^{-1}=\)', answer_matrix(3,3,5) ) \} \{ mbox( '\(B^{-1}=\)', answer_matrix(3,3,5) ) \} 
\{ mbox( '\(C^{-1}=\)', answer_matrix(6,6,5) ) \} 
$ECENTER
END_TEXT
